<% content_for(:title, "The Lab") %>

<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">

  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="mb-12">
    <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-orange-900/30 border border-orange-800/50 mb-6">
      <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-orange-500 animate-pulse"></span>
      <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-orange-400 uppercase tracking-wide">Day One · Live Experiment</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white tracking-tight leading-tight">The Lab</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-400 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
      A live experiment in human-directed agent teams. This site is the experiment &mdash; built, tested,
      and secured by AI agents under human direction. Watch how it works.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- The Premise -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">The premise</h2>
    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-gray-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        The line between building software and testing it is dissolving. Soon &mdash; sooner than most
        people think &mdash; the durable skill won't be writing code or writing tests. It will be
        <em class="text-gray-200 not-italic font-semibold">orchestrating the agents that do both</em>,
        and having the judgment to know when they got it right.
      </p>
      <p>
        I've spent 25 years in test automation, training my pattern-recognition on what software gets
        wrong. That judgment is the moat. Anyone can spin up Claude. Very few people have spent two
        decades watching code break in production.
      </p>
      <p>
        Agent44 Labs is the public version of me figuring this out. Instead of theorizing about agent
        orchestration, I'm running it on a system you're currently looking at. Every commit, every test
        run, every security scan, every bug an agent catches &mdash; that's the demo. Don't trust. Verify.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Setup -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">The setup</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900 p-5">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-orange-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Hardware</div>
        <p class="text-white font-semibold">One Mac mini</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Dedicated to running the agent team. Named <span class="text-gray-300">agent44</span>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900 p-5">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-orange-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Stack</div>
        <p class="text-white font-semibold">Claude + Claude Code</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Anthropic's agent-native CLI. The team will grow from here.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900 p-5">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-orange-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Codebase</div>
        <p class="text-white font-semibold">This Rails app</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">agent44labs.com is the test subject. Dogfood, all the way down.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Where We Are -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Where we are right now</h2>
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900 p-8">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-orange-900/50 border border-orange-800 flex items-center justify-center">
          <span class="text-orange-400 font-bold">1</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-semibold">Day One</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500"><%= Date.current.strftime("%B %-d, %Y") %></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        Hardware is set up. The Mac mini is running. Claude Code is installed. The agent team has not
        yet shipped a single line of code to this site.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mt-3">
        That changes from here. Every commit an agent authors will be tagged. Every test it writes
        will be tracked. Every time it gets something wrong, that goes in Pulse with my notes on why.
        This page will fill up with real activity as the experiment runs.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mt-4 font-medium">
        You are reading this on the very codebase the agents are about to start working on. Bookmark it
        and check back.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Plan -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">The plan</h2>
    <ol class="space-y-4">
      <% [
        ["Tag every commit", "Human-authored, agent-authored, or co-authored. From day one. No retroactive cleanup."],
        ["Start tiny", "Agents open PRs against the smallest possible scope first &mdash; copy edits, dependency bumps, test additions. Build the loop before expanding the surface area."],
        ["Wire in security scanners", "Brakeman, bundler-audit, secrets scanning. An agent runs them on a schedule, opens issues for findings, and writes the first-pass fix."],
        ["Let agents write their own tests", "Cassandra (the test agent, when she exists) writes Playwright coverage for what the human and other agents ship."],
        ["Publish everything in Pulse", "What worked. What didn't. What I had to step in for. The lab notes are the product."],
        ["Expand the loop", "Once the small scope is bulletproof, give agents more surface area. Eventually: features. Eventually: deploys with human approval. Eventually: deploys without."]
      ].each_with_index do |(title, body), i| %>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 flex items-center justify-center mt-0.5">
            <span class="text-xs font-bold text-gray-400"><%= i + 1 %></span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold"><%= title %></h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mt-0.5"><%= body.html_safe %></p>
          </div>
        </li>
      <% end %>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- AI Agent Engineer Salary Tally -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">What the next role pays</h2>
      <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-blue-400">Live · last 90d</span>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
      The scraper hunts for "AI Agent Engineer"-class roles &mdash; titles like
      <em>AI agent engineer, applied AI engineer, LLM engineer, agent architect,
      forward-deployed AI engineer</em>. People paid to build and direct teams of agents.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-8">
      <% [
        ["AI Agent Engineer",       @director_salary, "blue"],
        ["AI-Augmented Automation", @ai_salary,       "purple"],
        ["Traditional Automation",  @trad_salary,     "gray"]
      ].each do |label, stats, accent| %>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900 p-5">
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-<%= accent %>-400 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2"><%= label %></div>
          <% if stats[:with_salary].to_i > 0 %>
            <p class="text-3xl font-black text-white">$<%= number_with_delimiter(stats[:median]) %></p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">median &middot; <%= stats[:with_salary] %> of <%= stats[:total] %> postings list pay</p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-400 space-y-0.5">
              <div>p25: $<%= number_with_delimiter(stats[:p25]) %></div>
              <div>p75: $<%= number_with_delimiter(stats[:p75]) %></div>
              <div>max: $<%= number_with_delimiter(stats[:max]) %></div>
            </div>
          <% else %>
            <p class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-600">&mdash;</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">
              <%= stats[:total].to_i.zero? ? "No postings yet" : "#{stats[:total]} postings, none with salary data" %>
            </p>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <% if @recent_director_jobs.any? %>
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Recent AI agent engineer postings</h3>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900 divide-y divide-gray-800">
        <% @recent_director_jobs.each do |job| %>
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-4">
            <div class="min-w-0 flex-1 mr-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-white truncate"><%= link_to job.title, job_path(job), class: "hover:text-orange-400 transition" %></p>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-0.5"><%= job.company %> &middot; <%= job.location.presence || "Remote" %></p>
            </div>
            <% if job.salary.present? %>
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 whitespace-nowrap"><%= job.salary %></span>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    <% else %>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-dashed border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-6 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">No AI agent engineer roles in the index yet. The classifier just shipped &mdash; check back after the next scrape run.</p>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </section>

  <!-- Market Context -->
  <% if @ai_demand_meter.present? && @ai_demand_meter[:total].to_i > 0 %>
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Why now</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
        The job market is still asking for what worked yesterday. The lab is for what's coming next.
      </p>
      <%= render "shared/ai_demand_meter", meter: @ai_demand_meter, label: "AI-augmented vs traditional roles · last 30 days" %>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
        Look at that split. Most postings still describe the old world. The interesting question
        isn't <em>"what skills does the market want?"</em> &mdash; it's <em>"who's going to build the thing the
        market doesn't yet know how to ask for?"</em>
      </p>
    </section>
  <% end %>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-800 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 to-gray-950 p-8 text-center">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Follow along</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-gray-400 max-w-md mx-auto">
      The lab notes go out in Pulse. Field reports from a 25-year tester learning to direct agents.
      In public. In real time.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-3">
      <%= link_to "Read Pulse →", posts_path,
            class: "inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white bg-orange-600 rounded-full hover:bg-orange-700 transition" %>
      <%= link_to "See the job market data", jobs_path,
            class: "inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-gray-300 border border-gray-700 rounded-full hover:border-orange-500 hover:text-orange-400 transition" %>
    </div>
  </section>

</div>
